WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:29.104 --> 00:00:31.357
Howdy there. Mr. Lee.

3
00:00:31.523 --> 00:00:33.776
What's this? Filipino New Year's?

4
00:00:34.360 --> 00:00:35.945
No. Why you say that?

5
00:00:36.028 --> 00:00:37.863
'Cause you're cooking a feast.

6
00:00:37.947 --> 00:00:40.449
I can smell it from the interstate.

7
00:00:40.783 --> 00:00:43.035
What is that? Barbecue?

8
00:00:43.244 --> 00:00:45.746
Yeah. But it not coming from here.

9
00:00:46.622 --> 00:00:48.249
What is that noise?

10
00:04:19.627 --> 00:04:22.213
What is your take on this. Jerry?

11
00:04:22.755 --> 00:04:25.257
The people will love it. Mr. President.

12
00:04:25.591 --> 00:04:30.179
Our conflict is whether we ambush
the 6:00 news or hold out for prime time.

13
00:04:30.346 --> 00:04:32.681
Screw the press.
This is a need-to-know situation.

14
00:04:32.765 --> 00:04:36.769
We should make it top secret.
and should move in with Defcon Four.

15
00:04:36.977 --> 00:04:38.854
We can't sit on this.

16
00:04:40.522 --> 00:04:42.983
General Casey. do you have an opinion?

17
00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:45.611
Well. sir...

18
00:04:45.778 --> 00:04:47.279
...do we know they are hostile?

19
00:04:47.363 --> 00:04:49.281
What do you mean?

20
00:04:49.698 --> 00:04:52.284
They have the planet surrounded
by thousands of warships!

21
00:04:52.368 --> 00:04:54.286
Do we know they're warships?

22
00:04:57.790 --> 00:05:00.876
Professor. what do we know about them?

23
00:05:02.545 --> 00:05:04.713
They're very advanced technologically.

24
00:05:04.797 --> 00:05:08.050
Which suggests. rightfully so.
that they're peaceful.

25
00:05:08.634 --> 00:05:13.013
An advanced civilization is.
by definition. not barbaric.

26
00:05:13.138 --> 00:05:14.640
Mr. President...

27
00:05:15.015 --> 00:05:16.559
...this is a great day.

28
00:05:16.642 --> 00:05:18.644
I and all my colleagues...

29
00:05:18.811 --> 00:05:20.563
...are extremely excited.

30
00:05:21.021 --> 00:05:21.939
Good.

31
00:05:23.148 --> 00:05:25.526
Extraterrestrial life.

32
00:05:26.652 --> 00:05:28.320
You're right. Jerry.

33
00:05:28.529 --> 00:05:31.031
The people are going to love it.

34
00:05:31.156 --> 00:05:33.534
This is a momentous occasion.

35
00:05:34.410 --> 00:05:35.244
Mr. President--

36
00:05:35.327 --> 00:05:37.162
We'll go all media on this.

37
00:05:37.329 --> 00:05:39.081
I'll wear my Cerruti suit.

38
00:05:39.248 --> 00:05:40.916
I'll need a good speech.

39
00:05:41.917 --> 00:05:43.335
Statesman-like...

40
00:05:43.669 --> 00:05:45.379
...historical and yet...

41
00:05:45.588 --> 00:05:47.590
...warm. neighborly.

42
00:05:47.756 --> 00:05:51.552
Abraham Lincoln meets
Leave it to Beaver. kind of thing.

43
00:05:53.053 --> 00:05:54.680
Are they too old-fashioned?

44
00:05:54.763 --> 00:05:56.348
No. I don't think so.

45
00:05:56.599 --> 00:06:00.060
This has got the colors but. no.
I don't think so.

46
00:06:00.185 --> 00:06:01.562
Not vivid enough.

47
00:06:01.770 --> 00:06:03.772
Nancy had this in the library.

48
00:06:03.939 --> 00:06:04.690
Yes. indeed.

49
00:06:04.773 --> 00:06:06.025
I don't think so.

50
00:06:06.108 --> 00:06:09.486
I thought perhaps the watered silk.
This week it's on sale.

51
00:06:09.862 --> 00:06:12.573
I hardly think I need worry about that.

52
00:06:12.698 --> 00:06:15.367
My husband is the leader of the free world.

53
00:06:16.577 --> 00:06:18.037
What do you think?

54
00:06:18.704 --> 00:06:22.750
Why don't you leave the Roosevelt Room
the way the Roosevelts wanted it.

55
00:06:23.459 --> 00:06:27.713
Because Eleanor Roosevelt was
too fond of chintz. That's why.

56
00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:30.216
Mother. this isn't your house.

57
00:06:30.382 --> 00:06:33.469
lf you're going to be a pest. I'll ignore you!

58
00:06:33.719 --> 00:06:34.845
Mrs. Dale?

59
00:06:57.284 --> 00:06:59.954
I saw you fight Sonny Liston in '69.

60
00:07:00.120 --> 00:07:01.205
Really?

61
00:07:01.372 --> 00:07:03.541
You were a nun back then?

62
00:07:03.707 --> 00:07:06.877
We've always been fight fans.
haven't we sisters?

63
00:07:07.211 --> 00:07:09.463
Byron Williams. telephone.

64
00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:10.714
I must go.

65
00:07:10.881 --> 00:07:13.384
You ladies have a nice time.

66
00:07:19.014 --> 00:07:20.349
Oh. Louise.

67
00:07:20.891 --> 00:07:23.060
Sorry to call you at work. but...

68
00:07:23.561 --> 00:07:27.731
...the boys haven't been home
in two nights. I don't know what to do.

69
00:07:27.898 --> 00:07:29.984
You're doing the best you can.

70
00:07:30.234 --> 00:07:31.986
They're just at that age.

71
00:07:34.071 --> 00:07:37.533
The casino manager's giving me
the evil eye. I've gotta go.

72
00:07:37.658 --> 00:07:39.410
I'll call you later. okay?

73
00:07:40.244 --> 00:07:43.414
Are you still cool on me
coming to Washington?

74
00:07:43.581 --> 00:07:45.249
'Course I am.

75
00:07:45.749 --> 00:07:48.335
You take care. okay? Bye.

76
00:08:04.268 --> 00:08:06.103
Must you drink in front of me?

77
00:08:06.186 --> 00:08:08.272
You're an adult. Just cope.

78
00:08:08.439 --> 00:08:11.609
It doesn't help me
that all we ever do is sit in bars.

79
00:08:11.775 --> 00:08:13.611
This is work. baby. okay?

80
00:08:13.777 --> 00:08:17.448
I'm checking the decor.
the lighting. the traffic flow.

81
00:08:17.615 --> 00:08:20.618
lf I'd known you'd turn into a crook.
I wouldn't have married you.

82
00:08:20.701 --> 00:08:22.620
I'm not a crook.

83
00:08:22.786 --> 00:08:24.955
I'm ambitious. There's a difference.

84
00:08:25.039 --> 00:08:27.791
lf you think you can make
a nickel in this town...

85
00:08:27.875 --> 00:08:31.629
...without knowing how to dally
around a few curves. well...

86
00:08:31.962 --> 00:08:34.632
...you know nothing
of the gambling industry.

87
00:08:36.133 --> 00:08:40.221
The Galaxy's going to be
the best hotel in Vegas.

88
00:08:40.387 --> 00:08:42.056
The best!

89
00:08:42.264 --> 00:08:43.140
I promise.

90
00:08:43.224 --> 00:08:45.809
But don't you realize what you're doing?
You're destroying the Earth!

91
00:08:45.893 --> 00:08:48.812
All this greed! This money system!

92
00:08:48.979 --> 00:08:51.148
You're destroying everything!

93
00:08:51.899 --> 00:08:53.817
Okay. Barbara. okay.

94
00:08:54.151 --> 00:08:56.237
Keep your voice down.

95
00:08:56.987 --> 00:08:58.989
I got friends here.

96
00:09:00.324 --> 00:09:01.283
Sugar!

97
00:09:01.659 --> 00:09:03.077
Hit me one more time.

98
00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:04.578
Stop flirting with the waitress.

99
00:09:04.662 --> 00:09:05.996
God. Here.

100
00:09:07.581 --> 00:09:09.333
Go over to the roulette...

101
00:09:10.918 --> 00:09:12.670
...play our anniversary...

102
00:09:12.753 --> 00:09:14.838
...and stay off of black.

103
00:09:18.008 --> 00:09:18.842
Thanks.

104
00:09:27.393 --> 00:09:30.062
Make it quick.
we go out live in ten minutes.

105
00:09:30.896 --> 00:09:33.274
What? The actual president?

106
00:09:33.482 --> 00:09:34.650
Cutting in?

107
00:09:38.904 --> 00:09:42.074
Budget negotiations may be dead
in the water after this week.

108
00:09:42.157 --> 00:09:43.784
Hair looks good.

109
00:09:45.160 --> 00:09:46.245
I like the hair.

110
00:09:46.328 --> 00:09:48.497
...quote. ''factually-challenged. ''

111
00:09:49.331 --> 00:09:51.083
Yeah. Stone. Speak.

112
00:09:51.250 --> 00:09:52.751
Jason. hi. it's me.

113
00:09:53.919 --> 00:09:55.379
You wearing a bra?

114
00:09:55.838 --> 00:09:59.633
Listen. this is big. President Dale
is cutting into my show today.

115
00:10:01.260 --> 00:10:04.138
That's absurd. Why would he stoop
to being on ''Today in Fashion''?

116
00:10:04.221 --> 00:10:05.681
He's interrupting everybody.

117
00:10:05.764 --> 00:10:09.184
I don't know. it's some sort of
an emergency announcement.

118
00:10:09.351 --> 00:10:12.062
This doesn't make sense.
He should talk to us.

119
00:10:13.105 --> 00:10:15.149
White House is coming out live.

120
00:10:16.108 --> 00:10:18.944
Good evening. my fellow Americans.

121
00:10:19.278 --> 00:10:22.948
I apologize for interrupting
your regular programs...

122
00:10:23.115 --> 00:10:26.118
...but I have a very important
announcement to make.

123
00:10:26.619 --> 00:10:29.705
Many important things have happened
to me in my life:

124
00:10:30.206 --> 00:10:32.458
My graduation from Princeton...

125
00:10:32.958 --> 00:10:36.462
...the day that Marsha said
she would be my wife...

126
00:10:36.629 --> 00:10:38.881
...the birth of our daughter Taffy.

127
00:10:39.048 --> 00:10:40.049
Thanks. Dad.

128
00:10:40.132 --> 00:10:44.803
And the news that I have heard today
ranks right up there.

129
00:10:45.054 --> 00:10:47.306
A powerful memory is in the making.

130
00:10:47.973 --> 00:10:49.725
Not just for me...

131
00:10:49.892 --> 00:10:51.727
...but for all mankind.

132
00:10:52.019 --> 00:10:53.020
Today...

133
00:10:53.062 --> 00:10:56.649
...an extraordinary discovery
was made by the Hubble telescope.

134
00:10:58.776 --> 00:11:01.695
The data from the Hubble was decoded...

135
00:11:02.530 --> 00:11:07.159
...then analyzed by the most
powerful computers at MIT.

136
00:11:07.785 --> 00:11:10.037
The images are undeniable.

137
00:11:10.538 --> 00:11:13.707
We are entering the dawn of a new era.

138
00:11:14.875 --> 00:11:18.712
Frame enlargements provide
an astonishing sight.

139
00:11:18.963 --> 00:11:23.551
A fleet of vehicles.
which can best be described as...

140
00:11:23.801 --> 00:11:25.386
...flying saucers.

141
00:11:25.553 --> 00:11:28.722
Come on! Come on!
Papa needs a new pair of shoes!

142
00:11:31.725 --> 00:11:34.395
Hey. am I the only one
shooting craps here?

143
00:11:34.562 --> 00:11:38.274
We hope we will have the chance
to meet with them.

144
00:11:38.440 --> 00:11:41.193
This is the perfect summation
to the 20th Century....

145
00:11:41.277 --> 00:11:42.695
Martians.

146
00:11:43.279 --> 00:11:45.197
This is great.

147
00:11:45.614 --> 00:11:48.367
Please. come to Earth. Please.

148
00:11:49.034 --> 00:11:50.369
We need you.

149
00:11:54.540 --> 00:11:56.625
I got people coming in!

150
00:11:56.792 --> 00:11:59.628
Everybody wants to be part of this.

151
00:11:59.712 --> 00:12:02.548
Galaxy's going to be world class.

152
00:12:03.632 --> 00:12:04.967
And soon...

153
00:12:05.134 --> 00:12:08.137
...we will become one solar system.

154
00:12:08.637 --> 00:12:09.972
What the hell's he talking about?

155
00:12:10.055 --> 00:12:12.641
These flying saucers
have come from Mars...

156
00:12:14.393 --> 00:12:16.979
...and at their current course and speed...

157
00:12:17.313 --> 00:12:18.981
...will enter Earth's orbit in 16 hours.

158
00:12:19.064 --> 00:12:22.985
I've been thinking about Martians
when there weren't any.

159
00:12:23.402 --> 00:12:27.990
It is profoundly moving to know
there is intelligent life out there.

160
00:12:28.157 --> 00:12:29.658
Glad it's somewhere.

161
00:12:29.742 --> 00:12:33.579
Our world
will never feel quite the same again.

162
00:12:35.164 --> 00:12:36.415
Good night...

163
00:12:37.416 --> 00:12:39.293
...and God bless you all.

164
00:12:49.845 --> 00:12:51.180
This...

165
00:12:52.097 --> 00:12:53.682
...is intense.

166
00:12:56.352 --> 00:12:58.437
Shut up. Poppy. Shut up.

167
00:12:59.521 --> 00:13:00.856
Shut up!

168
00:13:01.523 --> 00:13:02.733
Jason Stone.

169
00:13:05.611 --> 00:13:06.862
It's for you.

170
00:13:08.697 --> 00:13:11.200
Poppy. honey. No. sweetie.

171
00:13:12.868 --> 00:13:15.037
That's right. Good girl.

172
00:13:18.958 --> 00:13:20.584
I could be there at...

173
00:13:21.210 --> 00:13:23.212
...I don't know. 11:00.

174
00:13:38.644 --> 00:13:42.147
They want me to interview
the professor from the White House.

175
00:13:42.815 --> 00:13:43.857
Kessler?

176
00:13:45.484 --> 00:13:46.569
Donald Kessler?

177
00:13:46.652 --> 00:13:48.696
Yeah. I think that was his name.

178
00:13:49.530 --> 00:13:50.906
You know. the science guy.

179
00:13:50.990 --> 00:13:52.825
This is nuts. this is....

180
00:13:53.158 --> 00:13:55.077
We should have got that guy.

181
00:13:55.494 --> 00:13:57.663
Your people are too slow.

182
00:13:58.998 --> 00:14:00.249
Right. Poppy?

183
00:14:24.106 --> 00:14:25.107
Finished!

184
00:14:25.190 --> 00:14:27.026
One minute. 57 seconds.

185
00:14:28.527 --> 00:14:30.779
-Didn't I tell you under two minutes?
-You did!

186
00:14:30.863 --> 00:14:31.864
You did!

187
00:14:31.947 --> 00:14:33.032
Hot damn.

188
00:14:33.782 --> 00:14:35.159
Want a doughnut?

189
00:14:35.451 --> 00:14:36.535
How old are they?

190
00:14:36.619 --> 00:14:38.037
Fresh baked. Monday.

191
00:14:38.120 --> 00:14:40.789
Richie. that's six days ago!

192
00:14:41.290 --> 00:14:42.708
Give me a couple.

193
00:14:46.462 --> 00:14:48.881
This Martian thing is pretty awesome.

194
00:14:49.048 --> 00:14:52.801
Did one of you traitors see my Muffy?

195
00:14:52.968 --> 00:14:54.720
Your brother's volunteering.

196
00:14:54.803 --> 00:14:56.972
As soon as I get back to the base.

197
00:14:57.056 --> 00:14:58.307
Volunteer for what?

198
00:14:58.390 --> 00:14:59.892
Martian detail.

199
00:15:00.976 --> 00:15:01.810
Cool.

200
00:15:01.894 --> 00:15:05.481
lf any Martians come around here.
I'll kick their butts!

201
00:15:17.910 --> 00:15:18.911
Jump!

202
00:15:28.462 --> 00:15:30.965
Folks.
we must make an unscheduled stop!

203
00:15:34.343 --> 00:15:35.511
It's Mama.

204
00:15:36.262 --> 00:15:39.515
Why are you here?
lf you ain't home. why ain't you in class?

205
00:15:39.598 --> 00:15:40.683
Class was cancelled.

206
00:15:40.766 --> 00:15:42.184
It was not!

207
00:15:42.351 --> 00:15:43.352
-Come here!
-Why?

208
00:15:43.435 --> 00:15:45.229
I'm not going to hurt you.

209
00:15:45.688 --> 00:15:46.939
Let go of him.

210
00:15:48.524 --> 00:15:50.943
Okay. Now just come here.

211
00:15:51.277 --> 00:15:52.528
Come here.

212
00:15:53.779 --> 00:15:55.447
Think it's smart to cut school?

213
00:15:55.531 --> 00:15:57.449
-What are you doing?
-Do you?

214
00:15:58.450 --> 00:15:59.618
No. it's dumb.

215
00:15:59.702 --> 00:16:01.537
You'll flunk! Go to jail!

216
00:16:01.704 --> 00:16:03.539
Get on the bus!

217
00:16:03.706 --> 00:16:04.790
Get on!

218
00:16:05.040 --> 00:16:07.543
I'll be tripping on you. Get back there.

219
00:16:07.710 --> 00:16:09.295
I don't want to hear anymore.

220
00:16:09.378 --> 00:16:10.462
I hate school.

221
00:16:10.546 --> 00:16:11.797
I heard that!

222
00:16:35.654 --> 00:16:36.739
Hi. there.

223
00:16:36.822 --> 00:16:37.990
Want a date?

224
00:16:38.157 --> 00:16:39.575
How about it?

225
00:16:39.825 --> 00:16:41.160
A date?

226
00:16:43.495 --> 00:16:44.788
It sounds good.

227
00:16:46.999 --> 00:16:48.834
The stress at work is...

228
00:16:49.168 --> 00:16:50.753
...unbelievable.

229
00:16:56.217 --> 00:16:57.968
May I speak to you in private?

230
00:16:58.052 --> 00:17:00.846
No. I must watch the floor.
What do you want?

231
00:17:01.347 --> 00:17:04.975
-I'm supporting a family back east.
-I thought you were divorced.

232
00:17:05.059 --> 00:17:07.853
I am. but I still have to take care of them.

233
00:17:08.729 --> 00:17:11.857
Things have been a little lean around here.

234
00:17:12.024 --> 00:17:13.984
I was wondering if I could get a raise?

235
00:17:14.068 --> 00:17:15.277
Out of the question.

236
00:17:15.361 --> 00:17:18.572
I'm an asset to this hotel.
They like me around here.

237
00:17:18.739 --> 00:17:20.407
You're a nice guy.

238
00:17:20.741 --> 00:17:24.578
But I can get Leon Spinks
or Buster Douglas for the same money.

239
00:17:25.037 --> 00:17:27.915
You better get moving.
You're on in five minutes.

240
00:17:37.091 --> 00:17:39.593
This show's going to get a great rating.

241
00:17:40.386 --> 00:17:41.679
It's all yours.

242
00:17:42.596 --> 00:17:47.560
ln certain circumstances the proposition
that two and two equals five...

243
00:17:47.726 --> 00:17:49.562
...is entirely legitimate.

244
00:17:51.272 --> 00:17:52.690
Call me Nathalie.

245
00:17:53.107 --> 00:17:55.901
And you. do please call me Donald.

246
00:17:57.278 --> 00:17:58.779
I admire your show.

247
00:18:01.240 --> 00:18:03.742
Really? You like my work?

248
00:18:04.118 --> 00:18:06.078
Yes. Very much.

249
00:18:06.245 --> 00:18:07.580
Why....

250
00:18:08.122 --> 00:18:09.915
Thank you.

251
00:18:10.082 --> 00:18:11.834
Coming out of commercial.

252
00:18:11.917 --> 00:18:13.627
In five...four...

253
00:18:13.794 --> 00:18:15.462
...three...two....

254
00:18:15.546 --> 00:18:18.966
Welcome back.
We're with Professor Donald Kessler.

255
00:18:20.926 --> 00:18:24.096
He's the chairman
of the American Academy...

256
00:18:24.263 --> 00:18:26.640
...of Astronautics.

257
00:18:27.808 --> 00:18:29.143
Professor...

258
00:18:29.435 --> 00:18:32.813
...isn't it weird that we sent
a space probe to Mars...

259
00:18:32.980 --> 00:18:35.065
...and we didn't even find anyone?

260
00:18:35.149 --> 00:18:37.151
Well. not really...

261
00:18:37.318 --> 00:18:38.527
...Nathalie.

262
00:18:38.986 --> 00:18:41.322
We didn't get into the canals.

263
00:18:41.488 --> 00:18:43.532
The Martian canals are canyons.

264
00:18:43.782 --> 00:18:45.951
Some are over 100 miles deep.

265
00:18:46.160 --> 00:18:50.998
The Martian civilization has clearly
developed under the planet's surface.

266
00:18:51.332 --> 00:18:54.877
Their science and technology
