I surrender!

538
00:42:31.752 --> 00:42:34.338
No. it ain't happening! It didn't happen!

539
00:43:31.187 --> 00:43:33.355
Holy Mother of God!

540
00:43:34.023 --> 00:43:35.482
Did you see that?

541
00:43:35.649 --> 00:43:39.111
We should hit these assholes
with everything we've got. sir.

542
00:43:39.695 --> 00:43:41.238
Sir. Mr. President.
I know this seems terrible...

543
00:43:41.322 --> 00:43:43.282
...but let's not be too rash.

544
00:43:43.365 --> 00:43:44.909
We should nuke them!

545
00:43:45.367 --> 00:43:48.162
We must establish
a line of communication first.

546
00:43:48.829 --> 00:43:50.539
Set up a town hall.

547
00:43:50.706 --> 00:43:52.750
We'll get the public's opinion.

548
00:43:54.710 --> 00:43:56.503
What do you think?

549
00:43:58.214 --> 00:44:00.007
Kick the crap out of them.

550
00:44:01.508 --> 00:44:03.135
Ladies and gentlemen...

551
00:44:03.219 --> 00:44:05.763
...it may be a cultural misunderstanding.

552
00:44:06.513 --> 00:44:08.516
Maybe to them. doves mean war.

553
00:44:10.434 --> 00:44:13.437
We all saw how they reacted to that dove.

554
00:44:13.771 --> 00:44:15.272
It frightened them.

555
00:44:15.689 --> 00:44:17.858
He did say that...

556
00:44:19.860 --> 00:44:22.029
...''We come in peace.''

557
00:44:31.872 --> 00:44:33.958
The new computer's ready.

558
00:44:34.124 --> 00:44:36.126
Okay. let's do it.

559
00:44:36.293 --> 00:44:38.879
I know we're making the right decision.

560
00:44:41.882 --> 00:44:43.384
Ready to transmit.

561
00:44:45.469 --> 00:44:49.223
This is the president of the United States.

562
00:44:50.140 --> 00:44:51.976
I'm speaking in the hope...

563
00:44:52.142 --> 00:44:55.521
...that what happened earlier today
in the Nevada desert...

564
00:44:55.896 --> 00:44:59.066
...was a cultural misunderstanding.

565
00:44:59.900 --> 00:45:02.820
There can be no doubt
that we two peoples...

566
00:45:02.987 --> 00:45:06.240
...have a great deal to offer one another.

567
00:45:06.407 --> 00:45:08.409
You must be as excited as we...

568
00:45:08.576 --> 00:45:11.787
...to find intelligent life in the solar system.

569
00:45:12.913 --> 00:45:14.832
Let me make it clear.

570
00:45:14.999 --> 00:45:16.667
You have nothing...

571
00:45:16.834 --> 00:45:18.836
...to fear from us.

572
00:45:19.253 --> 00:45:22.423
Our customs may be strange to you...

573
00:45:22.590 --> 00:45:25.259
...but we mean no harm.

574
00:46:37.248 --> 00:46:39.833
When the investors fly in...

575
00:46:40.334 --> 00:46:43.003
...I would like for them each to be...

576
00:46:44.338 --> 00:46:45.839
...met by a limo.

577
00:46:46.840 --> 00:46:49.260
Top of the line cars...

578
00:46:49.843 --> 00:46:52.179
...leather interiors...

579
00:46:52.763 --> 00:46:55.182
...Corinthian. if they got it.

580
00:46:56.016 --> 00:46:59.436
Are you still spinning your wheels
on that cockamamie hotel?

581
00:47:00.855 --> 00:47:02.106
Hello!

582
00:47:02.773 --> 00:47:04.775
The Martians have attacked!

583
00:47:04.942 --> 00:47:09.029
This was no misunderstanding.
I was there. I saw it.

584
00:47:09.196 --> 00:47:11.615
Look. you're worried about yesterday.

585
00:47:11.949 --> 00:47:13.951
I'm worried about tomorrow.

586
00:47:14.118 --> 00:47:17.705
The Martians land on Earth.
they'll need a place to stay.

587
00:47:17.872 --> 00:47:19.582
Just like everyone else.

588
00:47:20.374 --> 00:47:21.876
My God.

589
00:47:23.210 --> 00:47:25.963
Maybe we should all be destroyed.

590
00:47:26.964 --> 00:47:30.134
The human race doesn't deserve to live.

591
00:47:37.141 --> 00:47:38.309
Ethel...

592
00:47:38.475 --> 00:47:40.227
...that reminds me.

593
00:47:40.394 --> 00:47:42.813
I'd like the limos to be stocked...

594
00:47:42.980 --> 00:47:46.066
...with every kind of alcohol
known to man.

595
00:47:46.233 --> 00:47:48.986
And top it off with a bottle of Dom...

596
00:47:49.153 --> 00:47:50.654
...on ice.

597
00:47:51.655 --> 00:47:54.909
What confounds me most of all
is the lack of genitalia.

598
00:47:55.075 --> 00:47:56.994
Down here is the aorta.

599
00:47:57.161 --> 00:47:59.663
Up here we have the sphinx.

600
00:47:59.997 --> 00:48:03.167
Notice the highly developed
nerve system here.

601
00:48:03.334 --> 00:48:06.837
This explains. of course.
the cerebral arteries.

602
00:48:07.004 --> 00:48:10.674
And if we notice down here.
behind the optic chiasm...

603
00:48:11.425 --> 00:48:13.510
...several glands....

604
00:48:17.264 --> 00:48:19.099
Very curious.

605
00:49:01.725 --> 00:49:06.313
''He who believes in me.
though he die. yet shall he live.

606
00:49:07.231 --> 00:49:11.235
''And whoever lives and believes in me
shall never die.''

607
00:49:12.403 --> 00:49:15.739
Billy-Glenn Norris gave his life
defending our country.

608
00:49:15.906 --> 00:49:17.825
Why did it have to be him?

609
00:49:17.992 --> 00:49:21.996
He's a true American hero.
May God rest his soul.

610
00:49:23.664 --> 00:49:25.499
Ready! Aim.

611
00:49:27.084 --> 00:49:28.085
Fire!

612
00:49:29.503 --> 00:49:30.588
Aim!

613
00:49:30.921 --> 00:49:32.006
Fire!

614
00:49:44.685 --> 00:49:45.895
Hello?

615
00:49:46.061 --> 00:49:49.440
Byron! Is everything all right?
You still coming tomorrow?

616
00:49:49.523 --> 00:49:53.027
Just try and stop me.
That plane arrives at 4:00 p.m.

617
00:49:53.235 --> 00:49:54.737
Are the kids there?

618
00:49:54.904 --> 00:49:56.238
Yeah. hold on.

619
00:49:59.408 --> 00:50:01.076
-Me first.
-No. me.

620
00:50:04.705 --> 00:50:05.497
Hey. Dad.

621
00:50:05.581 --> 00:50:07.583
Who's that? Neville?

622
00:50:08.250 --> 00:50:09.251
How are you?

623
00:50:09.335 --> 00:50:11.253
We're going to the White House.

624
00:50:11.337 --> 00:50:12.922
The White House?

625
00:50:13.088 --> 00:50:14.340
Yeah. tomorrow.

626
00:50:14.506 --> 00:50:16.508
-Give it back!
-Leave me alone.

627
00:50:16.675 --> 00:50:18.928
It's a school thing. like a tour.

628
00:50:19.094 --> 00:50:22.014
So you're still going to school
once in a while?

629
00:50:23.516 --> 00:50:24.934
Give me your ma again.

630
00:50:25.017 --> 00:50:26.018
Hold on.

631
00:50:26.101 --> 00:50:26.936
Mom.

632
00:50:27.186 --> 00:50:29.939
-You always get to the phone first.
-So what?

633
00:50:30.606 --> 00:50:32.191
I'm first to the game.

634
00:50:34.276 --> 00:50:37.363
Why are you wasting this phone time?
I'll see you tomorrow.

635
00:50:37.446 --> 00:50:40.032
But there's something
I want to say to you.

636
00:50:40.199 --> 00:50:42.618
Just 'cause I feel like saying it.

637
00:50:42.868 --> 00:50:44.078
What's that?

638
00:50:44.787 --> 00:50:46.205
I love you.

639
00:50:48.040 --> 00:50:49.875
I love you too. Byron.

640
00:50:50.042 --> 00:50:53.128
Now stop wasting money!
I'll see you tomorrow!

641
00:51:10.646 --> 00:51:12.147
They're responding.

642
00:51:15.484 --> 00:51:17.486
A message from the Martians.

643
00:51:19.905 --> 00:51:20.823
Really?

644
00:51:20.906 --> 00:51:22.992
They've issued a formal apology.

645
00:51:24.910 --> 00:51:26.996
This is great!

646
00:51:27.746 --> 00:51:29.665
I told you this would happen.

647
00:51:29.832 --> 00:51:34.003
The Martian ambassador feels terrible
and wants to speak to Congress.

648
00:51:34.169 --> 00:51:35.754
That's good. isn't it?

649
00:51:35.921 --> 00:51:37.423
You bet.

650
00:51:38.007 --> 00:51:40.342
It's a victory for our administration.

651
00:52:54.917 --> 00:52:56.502
Ladies and gentlemen.

652
00:52:56.669 --> 00:52:59.755
This is a proud day for all Americans.

653
00:53:00.339 --> 00:53:03.592
This is a hell of a photo-op. Jerry.

654
00:53:04.176 --> 00:53:06.345
Are you sure I shouldn't be there?

655
00:53:06.512 --> 00:53:10.266
The Secret Service don't want
the executive branch...

656
00:53:10.432 --> 00:53:13.519
...and the legislative branch
in the same room.

657
00:53:14.603 --> 00:53:17.606
The Martian ambassador
is going to say a few words.

658
00:53:18.190 --> 00:53:20.359
Come on down. Mr. Ambassador!

659
00:54:28.427 --> 00:54:30.137
Mr. Ambassador. please!

660
00:54:35.935 --> 00:54:36.936
Please!

661
00:54:37.186 --> 00:54:39.104
This doesn't make sense!

662
00:54:39.271 --> 00:54:41.273
It's not logical! It's not--

663
00:54:43.275 --> 00:54:45.027
Guess it wasn't the dove.

664
00:54:46.946 --> 00:54:47.863
Fire!

665
00:54:53.702 --> 00:54:55.704
They blew up Congress!

666
00:55:17.810 --> 00:55:19.895
Why'd they do that?

667
00:55:20.104 --> 00:55:22.982
Maybe they don't like the human being.

668
00:55:40.958 --> 00:55:42.459
Hello. gentlemen.

669
00:55:42.626 --> 00:55:44.795
Nice of you to come on...

670
00:55:44.962 --> 00:55:46.797
...such short notice.

671
00:55:47.715 --> 00:55:49.216
General Decker...

672
00:55:49.383 --> 00:55:51.802
...it seems I owe you an apology.

673
00:55:52.052 --> 00:55:54.722
We all make mistakes. Mr. President.

674
00:55:54.889 --> 00:55:56.807
Not anymore.

675
00:55:57.141 --> 00:56:00.311
We're going to take charge of this thing!

676
00:56:00.561 --> 00:56:02.938
Excellent. I have prepared the order.

677
00:56:03.647 --> 00:56:04.815
What's this?

678
00:56:04.899 --> 00:56:08.235
Your executive order for full use
of our nuclear deterrent.

679
00:56:11.906 --> 00:56:14.491
Are you crazy? I'm not starting a war!

680
00:56:14.658 --> 00:56:18.746
We're already at war. sir! We have
to nuke them! We must nuke them now!

681
00:56:19.997 --> 00:56:23.417
General Decker. if you do not shut up...

682
00:56:23.834 --> 00:56:26.086
...I'll relieve you of your command.

683
00:56:26.253 --> 00:56:28.088
We must strike now. sir!

684
00:56:28.255 --> 00:56:30.257
Annihilate! Kill! Kill!

685
00:56:30.758 --> 00:56:31.759
Shut up!

686
00:56:31.926 --> 00:56:34.178
Shut up! Shut up!

687
00:56:59.870 --> 00:57:01.038
Now...

688
00:57:02.873 --> 00:57:05.376
...I want the people to know...

689
00:57:05.543 --> 00:57:08.796
...that they still have two out of three
branches of government...

690
00:57:08.879 --> 00:57:11.549
...working for them. and that ain't bad.

691
00:57:11.715 --> 00:57:16.637
I want the people to know
that the schools will still be open. okay?

692
00:57:17.221 --> 00:57:19.557
And I want the people to know...

693
00:57:19.723 --> 00:57:22.810
...that the garbage will still be carried out.

694
00:57:22.977 --> 00:57:24.645
And I want a cop...

695
00:57:24.812 --> 00:57:26.230
...on every corner.

696
00:57:26.313 --> 00:57:28.148
Which. incidentally...

697
00:57:28.315 --> 00:57:30.651
...we would already have...

698
00:57:30.818 --> 00:57:33.821
...if they had listened to me
in the last election.

699
00:57:36.991 --> 00:57:38.325
Jerry...

700
00:57:38.492 --> 00:57:40.661
...how soon can we go on the air?

701
00:57:46.166 --> 00:57:48.669
My fellow Americans.

702
00:57:49.169 --> 00:57:51.338
It is with a heavy heart...

703
00:57:51.505 --> 00:57:53.924
...that I speak to you this afternoon.

704
00:57:54.091 --> 00:57:55.342
As you know...

705
00:57:55.426 --> 00:58:00.347
...earlier today the Martian ambassador
and his confederates...

706
00:58:00.598 --> 00:58:02.349
...attacked and killed...

707
00:58:02.516 --> 00:58:06.687
...many of your representatives
on Capitol Hill.

708
00:58:07.271 --> 00:58:11.942
I will be conferring
with other world leaders as time goes on.

709
00:58:12.693 --> 00:58:16.614
And rest assured that. working together...

710
00:58:17.031 --> 00:58:19.700
...we will soon come out...

711
00:58:20.618 --> 00:58:23.537
...at a very real outcome.

712
00:58:25.789 --> 00:58:27.208
Thank you.

713
00:58:56.237 --> 00:58:57.988
Nathalie. is that you?

714
00:58:58.739 --> 00:58:59.990
Yes.

715
00:59:00.157 --> 00:59:01.325
How're you?

716
00:59:03.369 --> 00:59:05.454
Not terribly good. I'm afraid.

717
00:59:07.331 --> 00:59:09.083
May I ask you a question?

718
00:59:11.919 --> 00:59:13.504
Of course you can.

719
00:59:14.672 --> 00:59:17.091
Were you flirting with me on the show?

720
00:59:17.341 --> 00:59:18.509
Because...

721
00:59:18.759 --> 00:59:20.177
...if you were...

722
00:59:20.261 --> 00:59:22.096
...I just want you to know...

723
00:59:22.179 --> 00:59:24.014
...that I liked it.

724
00:59:25.516 --> 00:59:26.767
You did?

725
00:59:26.934 --> 00:59:27.935
Really?

726
00:59:28.018 --> 00:59:31.438
Because. you know.
I've watched you on TV quite a bit and...

727
00:59:31.522 --> 00:59:32.898
...well. I've...

728
00:59:33.357 --> 00:59:36.360
...had something of
a schoolboycrush on you for...

729
00:59:36.527 --> 00:59:37.778
...oh. gosh...

730
00:59:37.945 --> 00:59:39.196
...ages.

731
01:00:20.321 --> 01:00:21.447
Hi. there.

732
01:00:21.655 --> 01:00:24.074
Are you interested in the White House?

733
01:00:29.246 --> 01:00:31.749
I work there. I'm the press secretary.

734
01:00:31.916 --> 01:00:33.083
Jerry Ross.

735
01:00:33.834 --> 01:00:35.628
Have you ever heard of me?

736
01:00:37.254 --> 01:00:39.882
You wouldn't believe
the pressure of my job.

737
01:00:41.592 --> 01:00:43.761
It's nice to see a new face.

738
01:00:51.519 --> 01:00:52.937
Are you doing anything?

739
01:00:53.020 --> 01:00:55.105
'Cause if you want. I...

740
01:00:55.272 --> 01:00:57.316
...could give you a personalized tour.

741
01:00:57.399 --> 01:00:58.943
Would you like that?

742
01:01:01.320 --> 01:01:04.406
Hey. Mitch. it's me. Can you let me in?

743
01:01:08.244 --> 01:01:10.496
Hello. Mr. Ross. Sure.

744
01:01:10.663 --> 01:01:13.165
We're a little nervous here.
after what happened.

745
01:01:13.249 --> 01:01:14.333
Exactly.

746
01:01:23.676 --> 01:01:26.595
Many great men and women
have passed through here.

747
01:01:27.179 --> 01:01:29.348
Now we're passing through here.

748
01:01:29.849 --> 01:01:31.934
Feels good. don't it?

749
01:01:35.271 --> 01:01:37.106
You're very graceful.

750
01:01:37.857 --> 01:01:39.108
I like that.

751
01:01:46.782 --> 01:01:47.950
Come here.

752
01:02:08.470 --> 01:02:10.556
We call this the Kennedy Room.

753
01:02:14.894 --> 01:02:16.562
Pretty nifty. huh?

754
01:02:49.845 --> 01:02:51.096
So...

755
01:02:51.263 --> 01:02:52.848
...how about a drink?

756
01:03:22.962 --> 01:03:24.880
Getting more comfortable.

757
01:03:27.216 --> 01:03:28.634
Outstanding.

758
01:03:43.148 --> 01:03:44.733
How's my lady doing?

759
01:03:55.077 --> 01:03:57.162
Oh. missy. you're hot.

760
01:03:57.913 --> 01:04:00.332
Could we get that gum out of your mouth?

761
01:04:06.922 --> 01:04:08.257
My finger!

762
01:04:13.429 --> 01:04:16.265
Hello! Hello. operator?
This is an emergency!

763
01:04:16.432 --> 01:04:17.516
Help!

764
01:05:43.352 --> 01:05:44.520
Don't shoot!

765
01:05:49.024 --> 01:05:50.609
Don't worry. darling.

766
01:05:59.451 --> 01:06:00.536
Get down!

767
01:06:10.880 --> 01:06:12.298
Thank you. Mitch.

768
01:06:12.464 --> 01:06:13.674
It's my job.

769
01:07:07.937 --> 01:07:08.854
What's happening?

770
01:07:08.938 --> 01:07:12.358
They appear to be
in a highly agitated state.

771
01:07:12.525 --> 01:07:14.944
And I. I don't know.

772
01:07:15.611 --> 01:07:17.196
I honestly don't know.

773
01:07:17.363 --> 01:07:20.366
I don't know what's going on anymore.
This is frustrating.

774
01:07:20.449 --> 01:07:22.159
I'm not feeling myself.

775
01:07:22.535 --> 01:07:24.620
lf only I could hold you in my arms!

776
01:07:24.703 --> 01:07:26.288
Oh. Donald!

777
01:07:26.455 --> 01:07:28.082
I'm scared!

778
01:08:02.241 --> 01:08:03.325
Excuse me.

779
01:08:03.492 --> 01:08:06.328
You said you wanted to know
as soon as possible.

780
01:08:06.495 --> 01:08:07.580
What is it?

781
01:08:07.663 --> 01:08:08.914
It's NO2.

782
01:08:09.081 --> 01:08:10.833
Highly concentrated.

783
01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:12.334
Nitrogen.

784
01:08:12.835 --> 01:08:14.169
So...

785
01:08:14.420 --> 01:08:17.423
...that's how it could breathe
in our atmosphere.

786
01:08:18.257 --> 01:08:20.092
What's that noise?

787
01:08:52.082 --> 01:08:55.252
But. Theodore.
I simply do not feel that Lincoln....

788
01:08:55.669 --> 01:08:57.338
It's a full-scale invasion.

789
01:08:57.421 --> 01:08:59.173
We must get you to safety.

790
01:09:05.095 --> 01:09:06.347
Not this way?

791
01:09:06.430 --> 01:09:08.933
I'm sorry. there's a tour going through.

792
01:09:09.517 --> 01:09:13.521
The Blue Room is often considered
the most beautiful in the White House.

793
01:09:13.687 --> 01:09:16.857
It is often used by the president
to receive guests.

794
01:09:17.691 --> 01:09:20.694
It is furnished to represent
the period of James Monroe.

795
01:09:20.778 --> 01:09:21.987
What's that?

796
01:09:22.404 --> 01:09:23.739
That...

797
01:09:23.906 --> 01:09:26.492
...is a portrait of James Monroe.

798
01:10:18.377 --> 01:10:19.879
We lost Taffy!

799
01:10:24.466 --> 01:10:28.053
Keep moving.
we must get you to the back stairs!

800
01:10:34.560 --> 01:10:36.478
The Nancy Reagan chandelier!

801
01:10:55.456 --> 01:10:58.459
What are you gawking at?
Get that president out of here!

802
01:11:04.840 --> 01:11:06.842
I personally guarantee...

803
01:11:07.259 --> 01:11:10.721
...that you will get a complete return
on your investment...

804
01:11:10.846 --> 01:11:12.848
...within five months.

805
01:11:13.015 --> 01:11:14.934
Mr. Land. excuse me.

806
01:11:15.100 --> 01:11:18.354
Just a second. Sheik Rakula.

807
01:11:20.356 --> 01:11:21.106
Now...

808
01:11:21.190 --> 01:11:25.361
...even in a time of so-called
intergalactic emergency...

809
01:11:26.529 --> 01:11:27.863
...the people...

810
01:11:28.030 --> 01:11:30.699
...still want to roll them bones!

811
01:11:32.201 --> 01:11:33.702
I believe--

812
01:11:34.203 --> 01:11:36.038
Just five more minutes.

813
01:11:36.956 --> 01:11:39.959
What I'd like for you to do is to...

814
01:11:40.125 --> 01:11:43.462
...view our new.
state-of-the-art show room.

815
01:11:44.797 --> 01:11:47.132
It is out-of-sight!

816
01:11:48.717 --> 01:11:49.844
Gentlemen.

817
01:11:53.889 --> 01:11:55.891
There is no way...

818
01:11:56.058 --> 01:11:57.893
...that we can lose.

819
01:12:43.105 --> 01:12:46.442
''It's not unusual to be loved by anyone

820
01:12:48.277 --> 01:12:51.864
''It's not unusual to have fun with anyone

821
01:12:53.365 --> 01:12:56.952
''But when I see you hanging
about with anyone

822
01:12:58.829 --> 01:13:01.498
''It's not unusual to see me cry

823
01:13:03.417 --> 01:13:05.419
''I want to die''

824
01:13:06.253 --> 01:13:08.088
I've called you all day.

825
01:13:08.255 --> 01:13:09.673
The flight's been canceled.

826
01:13:09.757 --> 01:13:12.259
Byron. there's Martians everywhere!

827
01:13:13.177 --> 01:13:14.136
Hello?

828
01:13:15.763 --> 01:13:17.181
I can't hear you!

829
01:13:22.811 --> 01:13:24.563
I must get to Washington.

830
01:13:29.652 --> 01:13:31.445
Do you know anyone who can fly a plane?

831
01:13:31.529 --> 01:13:32.696
Your husband. Art.

832
01:13:32.780 --> 01:13:33.864
He's dead.

833
01:13:34.031 --> 01:13:35.574
I told him this would happen.

834
01:13:35.658 --> 01:13:37.826
I loaded the plane with supplies.

835
01:13:38.118 --> 01:13:42.456
I want to go to the Tahoe caves.
It's remote. the Martians won't find it.

836
01:13:42.873 --> 01:13:43.874
Where's the plane?

837
01:13:43.958 --> 01:13:46.710
Private airfield. Other side of the freeway.

838
01:13:46.877 --> 01:13:48.629
Will it fly to Washington?

839
01:13:48.796 --> 01:13:50.631
I want to go to Tahoe.

840
01:13:50.798 --> 01:13:52.633
''You find it happens

841
01:13:52.800 --> 01:13:54.969
''All the time

842
01:13:55.553 --> 01:13:57.972
''Love will never do

843
01:13:58.639 --> 01:14:00.641
''What you want it to

844
01:14:01.559 --> 01:14:03.561
''Why can't this crazy love

845
01:14:03.978 --> 01:14:05.980
''Be mine''

846
01:14:14.905 --> 01:14:16.240
Jesus Christ!

847
01:14:25.291 --> 01:14:26.792
Girls. get out!

848
01:14:36.051 --> 01:14:38.470
There's a Martian right behind me!

849
01:14:38.637 --> 01:14:41.307
You're Tom Jones! ''It Ain't Unusual.''

850
01:14:42.474 --> 01:14:43.559
Autograph?

851
01:14:43.642 --> 01:14:45.769
Anybody got a pen?

852
01:15:03.913 --> 01:15:05.247
Great punch.

853
01:15:05.414 --> 01:15:06.832
You'll need that gun.

854
01:15:06.916 --> 01:15:08.667
-I'm Tom Jones.
-Byron Williams.

855
01:15:08.751 --> 01:15:11.003
I saw you fight in Cardiff. Wales.

856
01:15:12.338 --> 01:15:13.506
You okay?

857
01:15:13.923 --> 01:15:16.175
-I need a drink.
-You and me both.

858
01:15:16.342 --> 01:15:18.344
-We better go.
-Can you fly a plane?

859
01:15:18.427 --> 01:15:19.345
Sure. Got one?

860
01:15:19.428 --> 01:15:20.513
She has.

861
01:15:40.032 --> 01:15:42.785
Don't run. we are your friends.

862
01:16:13.816 --> 01:16:15.401
Martians blew up the shop!

863
01:16:15.484 --> 01:16:16.402
You're kidding.

864
01:16:16.485 --> 01:16:17.570
Should I get Grandma?

865
01:16:17.653 --> 01:16:21.156
Forget her! She's halfway
to outer space already! Here!

866
01:16:21.323 --> 01:16:24.493
I'll tell you one thing.
They ain't getting the TV!

867
01:16:28.163 --> 01:16:31.000
The president of France is on line two.

868
01:16:34.837 --> 01:16:38.090
Mr. President. the president of France
is on line two.

869
01:16:38.257 --> 01:16:40.092
He says it's important.

870
01:16:45.681 --> 01:16:47.850
Hello. Maurice.

871
01:16:50.519 --> 01:16:52.188
I have good news.

872
01:16:52.354 --> 01:16:53.856
The Martian ambassador is here.

873
01:16:53.939 --> 01:16:56.192
We've negotiated a settlement.

874
01:16:58.194 --> 01:17:00.529
Maurice get out of the room.

875
01:17:00.696 --> 01:17:02.198
Get out. now!

876
01:17:47.826 --> 01:17:49.078
Mr. President.

877
01:17:51.497 --> 01:17:53.249
Mr. President.

878
01:17:53.415 --> 01:17:56.001
I need you to sign this!

879
01:18:00.756 --> 01:18:02.258
What is it?

880
01:18:02.424 --> 01:18:04.844
My last will and testament?

881
01:18:05.010 --> 01:18:09.014
It is an order to deploy
our nuclear capability. sir.

882
01:19:20.836 --> 01:19:22.755
What the hell was that?

883
01:21:05.065 --> 01:21:05.983
Look!

884
01:21:13.407 --> 01:21:14.658
What was that?

885
01:21:16.702 --> 01:21:17.786
Where you going?

886
01:21:17.870 --> 01:21:18.954
To get Grandma.

887
01:21:19.038 --> 01:21:20.998
Stay and defend this trailer!

888
01:21:21.081 --> 01:21:23.209
That's what Billy-Glenn would do.

889
01:21:23.375 --> 01:21:24.960
You're disgracing a hero!

890
01:21:25.044 --> 01:21:27.546
I don't care. I'm gonna go get grandma.

891
01:21:28.214 --> 01:21:29.590
Come back here!

892
01:21:42.895 --> 01:21:44.647
What in the hell is that?

893
01:21:52.112 --> 01:21:53.447
Cut it out!

894
01:21:58.953 --> 01:22:00.329
Stop it!

895
01:22:09.255 --> 01:22:10.381
-This way!
-No. this way!

896
01:22:10.464 --> 01:22:12.925
It's a short cut! The airfield's--

897
01:22:13.092 --> 01:22:15.594
Bullshit! The airfield's over there!

898
01:22:21.433 --> 01:22:25.354
Being dressed like King Tut
doesn't make you our leader!

899
01:22:25.479 --> 01:22:26.981
Look. this is wrong!

900
01:22:27.147 --> 01:22:30.985
We're lost! He led us down a maze!
I'm going back to the hotel.

901
01:22:31.151 --> 01:22:32.486
-This way!
-Wait!

902
01:22:32.653 --> 01:22:34.488
Where are you going?

903
01:22:34.655 --> 01:22:35.406
Come on.

904
01:22:35.489 --> 01:22:36.991
But. I like him.

905
01:22:43.455 --> 01:22:47.793
Assholes! Why'd I listen to them?
I should have stayed in the hotel.

906
01:22:48.377 --> 01:22:49.795
Shit!

907
01:22:52.506 --> 01:22:54.008
I surrender. okay?

908
01:22:54.508 --> 01:22:56.802
You understand what that means?

909
01:22:58.012 --> 01:23:00.681
Look! You're intelligent beings.

910
01:23:01.307 --> 01:23:03.517
Let's cut a deal. I can help.

911
01:23:03.684 --> 01:23:05.144
I'm a lawyer!

912
01:23:05.477 --> 01:23:08.898
You want to conquer the world.
you'll need lawyers. right?

913
01:23:10.524 --> 01:23:11.525
Here.

914
01:23:12.401 --> 01:23:14.028
You want my watch?

915
01:23:14.528 --> 01:23:17.198
Take it. Take it. It's a Rolex!

916
01:23:27.708 --> 01:23:29.168
Nice shot!

917
01:23:29.335 --> 01:23:30.753
Pity I was too late.

918
01:23:30.836 --> 01:23:32.713
Can I have the gun back?

919
01:23:32.922 --> 01:23:34.840
Give me the gun and come on!

920
01:24:49.623 --> 01:24:50.624
Grandma!

921
01:24:59.008 --> 01:25:00.301
Oh. my God!

922
01:25:14.440 --> 01:25:16.817
I think these guys are very sick.

923
01:25:17.651 --> 01:25:20.362
What's happening to them?
What's killing them?

924
01:25:21.822 --> 01:25:24.200
I think it must be my music.

925
01:25:31.999 --> 01:25:33.417
Quiet!

926
01:26:25.052 --> 01:26:27.638
You think you can do anything you want.

927
01:26:27.805 --> 01:26:29.223
You can't.

928
01:26:29.390 --> 01:26:30.224
Because...

929
01:26:30.307 --> 01:26:32.560
...we are human...

930
01:26:32.893 --> 01:26:33.894
...beings.

931
01:26:33.978 --> 01:26:37.565
And we have the United States Army...

932
01:26:38.566 --> 01:26:40.150
...that'll fight you...

933
01:26:40.234 --> 01:26:44.321
...to the last man!
And we'll never surrender!

934
01:26:48.158 --> 01:26:49.743
Do you hear me?

935
01:26:49.910 --> 01:26:52.830
We'll fight you on the beaches.
We'll fight you in the streets.

936
01:26:52.913 --> 01:26:55.416
We will never. never surrender!

937
01:26:55.583 --> 01:26:57.918
We will win!

938
01:26:58.085 --> 01:26:59.920
Democracy will survive!

939
01:27:00.171 --> 01:27:02.006
We will never. ever...

940
01:27:02.173 --> 01:27:03.757
...surrender!

941
01:27:03.924 --> 01:27:05.259
We will win!

942
01:27:05.426 --> 01:27:07.428
The eagle will be triumphant!

943
01:27:37.458 --> 01:27:38.959
Why...

944
01:27:39.210 --> 01:27:40.961
...are you doing this?

945
01:27:43.047 --> 01:27:44.215
Why?

946
01:27:45.382 --> 01:27:48.135
lsn't the universe big enough...

947
01:27:48.719 --> 01:27:50.387
...for both of us?

948
01:27:54.308 --> 01:27:56.393
What is wrong with you people?

949
01:27:59.313 --> 01:28:00.981
We could work together.

950
01:28:02.149 --> 01:28:04.235
Why be enemies?

951
01:28:05.236 --> 01:28:06.987
Because we're different?

952
01:28:08.072 --> 01:28:09.740
Is that why?

953
01:28:13.911 --> 01:28:16.580
Think of the things that we could do.

954
01:28:17.998 --> 01:28:20.918
Think how strong we would be!

955
01:28:22.753 --> 01:28:24.255
Earth...

956
01:28:25.089 --> 01:28:27.007
...and Mars...

957
01:28:28.092 --> 01:28:29.343
...together.

958
01:28:31.971 --> 01:28:34.807
There is nothing
that we could not accomplish.

959
01:28:35.850 --> 01:28:37.601
Think about it!

960
01:28:39.854 --> 01:28:41.772
Think about it!

961
01:28:43.274 --> 01:28:44.942
Why destroy...

962
01:28:45.776 --> 01:28:47.945
...when you can create?

963
01:28:49.280 --> 01:28:51.282
We can have it all...

964
01:28:52.116 --> 01:28:54.535
...or we can smash it all!

965
01:28:58.038 --> 01:28:59.540
Why can't we...

966
01:28:59.790 --> 01:29:02.042
...work out our differences?

967
01:29:03.294 --> 01:29:05.212
Why can't we...

968
01:29:05.546 --> 01:29:07.715
...work things out?

969
01:29:10.217 --> 01:29:12.386
Little people...

970
01:29:14.722 --> 01:29:16.807
...why can't we all just...

971
01:29:18.058 --> 01:29:19.810
...get along?

972
01:29:46.670 --> 01:29:47.880
What's this?

973
01:30:26.126 --> 01:30:28.712
Don't run. We are your friends.

974
01:30:30.297 --> 01:30:32.883
Don't run. We are your friends.

975
01:30:46.355 --> 01:30:48.190
Next stop. radio station.

976
01:30:51.110 --> 01:30:52.611
There it is!

977
01:30:53.279 --> 01:30:54.864
Let's move it!

978
01:31:12.798 --> 01:31:14.133
There it is.

979
01:31:15.467 --> 01:31:17.553
Go start it. Go with him.

980
01:31:17.720 --> 01:31:19.305
Cindy. come with me.

981
01:31:36.572 --> 01:31:38.157
Are you sure you can fly this?

982
01:31:38.240 --> 01:31:39.909
I think so. yeah.

983
01:31:42.328 --> 01:31:43.746
Who put that on?

984
01:31:45.080 --> 01:31:47.833
-It's stuck!
-Cindy. over here.

985
01:31:54.340 --> 01:31:55.508
Shit!

986
01:31:56.425 --> 01:31:58.761
They haven't seen us yet. Come here.

987
01:32:00.846 --> 01:32:02.264
Get in the plane.

988
01:32:02.681 --> 01:32:04.517
I'll distract them.

989
01:32:04.683 --> 01:32:06.936
The first chance you get. go.

990
01:32:07.102 --> 01:32:09.271
-I'm not leaving you!
-Just do it!

991
01:32:09.355 --> 01:32:11.357
I'll draw them away! Go!

992
01:32:11.524 --> 01:32:12.608
No!

993
01:32:12.775 --> 01:32:14.193
I said go!

994
01:32:18.948 --> 01:32:20.533
Oh. my God!

995
01:32:21.367 --> 01:32:22.701
What's he doing?

996
01:32:22.785 --> 01:32:23.702
He's flipped!

997
01:32:23.786 --> 01:32:25.704
He's going to throw them off
so we can escape.

998
01:32:25.788 --> 01:32:27.289
We can't leave him!

999
01:32:30.459 --> 01:32:31.544
No weapon!

1000
01:32:31.877 --> 01:32:34.046
No clown outfit!

1001
01:32:34.213 --> 01:32:35.464
Just me!

1002
01:32:36.048 --> 01:32:37.466
Byron Williams...

1003
01:32:38.133 --> 01:32:40.386
...heavyweight champion...

1004
01:32:40.970 --> 01:32:42.638
...of the world!

1005
01:33:53.334 --> 01:33:55.419
Something's happened.

1006
01:33:55.711 --> 01:33:57.796
Something's happened to Byron.

1007
01:34:14.188 --> 01:34:16.774
''When I'm calling you

1008
01:34:38.379 --> 01:34:41.924
''That means I offer my love to you''

1009
01:35:19.336 --> 01:35:20.754
Good-bye. my darling.

1010
01:35:20.838 --> 01:35:22.798
I wish things were different.

1011
01:35:23.591 --> 01:35:25.259
So do I.

1012
01:35:30.848 --> 01:35:32.183
Good-bye.

1013
01:35:32.600 --> 01:35:33.684
I love you.

1014
01:35:33.767 --> 01:35:35.686
I love you too. Nathalie.

1015
01:37:11.448 --> 01:37:13.033
Florence Norris...

1016
01:37:13.200 --> 01:37:16.370
...I present to you
the Congressional Medal of Honor...

1017
01:37:16.537 --> 01:37:18.789
...the nation's highest decoration.

1018
01:37:20.708 --> 01:37:24.295
Thank you.
but don't you dare let this happen again!

1019
01:37:25.796 --> 01:37:27.548
Richard Norris...

1020
01:37:27.715 --> 01:37:30.718
...on behalf of my parents.
who couldn't be here today...

1021
01:37:30.801 --> 01:37:33.304
...for saving the world from the Martians...

1022
01:37:33.387 --> 01:37:35.890
...I present to you the Medal of Honor.

1023
01:37:36.724 --> 01:37:38.809
Don't kiss me if you don't want.

1024
01:37:39.226 --> 01:37:40.728
I have to.

1025
01:37:43.898 --> 01:37:46.233
I prepared a speech. Is that okay?

1026
01:37:46.984 --> 01:37:49.069
Sure. that's very appropriate.

1027
01:37:53.908 --> 01:37:55.159
Hi. everybody.

1028
01:37:56.577 --> 01:37:57.828
I want to say--

1029
01:37:57.912 --> 01:38:00.498
Can you speak up? We can't hear you.

1030
01:38:00.998 --> 01:38:04.335
I want to say that there's
a lot of people in the world...

1031
01:38:04.418 --> 01:38:07.338
...that have done a lot more
than I have. and...

1032
01:38:07.505 --> 01:38:09.673
...they should be here now...

1033
01:38:09.924 --> 01:38:11.425
...getting a medal.

1034
01:38:13.427 --> 01:38:15.596
And I want to thank my grandma...

1035
01:38:15.763 --> 01:38:17.932
...for always being good to me...

1036
01:38:18.098 --> 01:38:21.018
...and for helping save the world
and everything.

1037
01:38:22.186 --> 01:38:25.439
So. I guess. like. now we just have to...

1038
01:38:25.606 --> 01:38:29.610
...start over and start rebuilding
everything. like our houses.

1039
01:38:29.777 --> 01:38:34.698
But I was thinking. maybe instead
of houses we could live in tepees.

1040
01:38:35.032 --> 01:38:37.201
Because it's better in many ways.

1041
01:38:40.788 --> 01:38:43.457
That's all I have to say. Thanks.

1042
01:38:45.376 --> 01:38:46.627
Was that okay?

1043
01:38:46.710 --> 01:38:47.795
Yeah.

1044
01:38:48.629 --> 01:38:50.339
Do you got a girlfriend?

1045
01:38:50.548 --> 01:38:51.549
No.

1046
01:38:52.967 --> 01:38:56.053
Give me a break.
Go on in there and clean your room.

1047
01:38:56.220 --> 01:38:58.889
I can't do this all by myself. Look at you.

1048
